<div id="review_3965171504" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3965171504" />
    <a title="Roxann" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42380587-roxann"><img alt="Roxann" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1429645114p2/42380587.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3965171504?book_show_action=true">May 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Roxann" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Roxann" href="/user/show/42380587-roxann">Roxann</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25171418-the-story-of-my-misfortunes-the-autobiography-of-peter-abelard">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3965171504" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13061406112542399996">The tale of Peter Abelard is a woeful tale. Abelard&apos;s general claim to fame is his relationship with Heloise, but this book is not about that. As the name declares, Historia Calamitatum (The story of my Misfortunes), is about his life which was filled with challenges. His relationship with Heloise is mentioned only 2-3 times in the book, so this is not the book to read if you are interested in that specific relationship, but it does give some insight into Abelard&apos;s approach to the world. While r</span>
  <span id="freeText13061406112542399996" style="display:none">The tale of Peter Abelard is a woeful tale. Abelard's general claim to fame is his relationship with Heloise, but this book is not about that. As the name declares, Historia Calamitatum (The story of my Misfortunes), is about his life which was filled with challenges. His relationship with Heloise is mentioned only 2-3 times in the book, so this is not the book to read if you are interested in that specific relationship, but it does give some insight into Abelard's approach to the world. While reading this book, it was difficult to know whether he was just paranoid or if everyone was really out to get him. I guess the crime that was visited upon him would suggest that he was not just paranoid. He seems quite full of himself, and it is not hard to see why he had trouble getting along in the world, but apparently he was very educated. This book also does not provide much insight into his religious beliefs of the time, and why they here so heretical. But, it is a short read and a good companion to the Letters of Abelard and Heloise. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13061406112542399996" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


