<div id="review_3571826931" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3571826931" />
    <a title="Paul Smith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14148102-paul-smith"><img alt="Paul Smith" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464598022p2/14148102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3571826931?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul Smith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul Smith" href="/user/show/14148102-paul-smith">Paul Smith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25171418-the-story-of-my-misfortunes-the-autobiography-of-peter-abelard">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3571826931" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9820477624481762307">This was a very entertaining short book i read on a lark, having not heard of it previously, and as it is not without a few surprises, I was well rewarded.<br/>It is perhaps a bit disappointing that the writer remains unaware of his own faults at the end of the book. If not for his self satisfaction, and disrespect of more established people he might have avoided half his troubles. But he had not finished at the point at which he wrote this letter, and one can hope he managed to learn his lesson in t</span>
  <span id="freeText9820477624481762307" style="display:none">This was a very entertaining short book i read on a lark, having not heard of it previously, and as it is not without a few surprises, I was well rewarded.<br />It is perhaps a bit disappointing that the writer remains unaware of his own faults at the end of the book. If not for his self satisfaction, and disrespect of more established people he might have avoided half his troubles. But he had not finished at the point at which he wrote this letter, and one can hope he managed to learn his lesson in the years to come.<br />Toward the end, i wonder if he was imagining assassins and a bit paranoid, especially because his latest enemies appeared to have the least motive, but i suppose asking for an outside perspective is a but much for book written in the twelfth century.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9820477624481762307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
