<div id="review_1374303368" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1374303368" />
    <a title="Dennis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24478928-dennis"><img alt="Dennis" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1374303368?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dennis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dennis" href="/user/show/24478928-dennis">Dennis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/21319696-historia-calamitatum---the-story-of-my-misfortunes">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1374303368" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4123167293370415067">Whereupon Abelard&apos;s contemporaries, namely St Anselm of Canterbury, occupy a lofty, almost supernatural status due to the primacy of their influential works, Abelard remains solidly real, relatable and worldly. In this autobiography, the woes of a man of colossal stature are laid bare in intimate detail, such that they bring him closer to earth, that one may feel a sense of connection with him, for human troubles transcend the ages. Within this compact work are the most moving, and harrowing acc</span>
  <span id="freeText4123167293370415067" style="display:none">Whereupon Abelard's contemporaries, namely St Anselm of Canterbury, occupy a lofty, almost supernatural status due to the primacy of their influential works, Abelard remains solidly real, relatable and worldly. In this autobiography, the woes of a man of colossal stature are laid bare in intimate detail, such that they bring him closer to earth, that one may feel a sense of connection with him, for human troubles transcend the ages. Within this compact work are the most moving, and harrowing accounts of a man whose brilliance in dialectics brings upon him much suffering. <br /><br />To paraphrase the intro, such a work is to be read that we may see through the power of contrast, how insignificant our troubles are in comparison to those who suffer greater.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4123167293370415067" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


